page.title: 01South and East of Lane End
page.content: The block is situated on the Chiltern Hills, convenient to the M40 motorway and consists of approximately half mixed deciduous woodland with beech predominating and half arable farmland. In the north-west is the village of Lane End which is primarily residential but has some light industry and two management/conference centres. Residential development has taken place recently at Lane End and at Booker in the north-east which is now effectively a suburb of High Wycombe. At Wycombe Air Park, Booker, club and glider flying takes place, giving rise to some noise complaints from local residents. Alongside the airfield is a garden centre and a small residential area which used to be RAF married quarters.
